ries of intimate conversations wherein lovers argue and act out their richly populated inner lives, addressing issues of gender, pleasure, communication, control, and sex.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aCanadian poetryy21st century. 7aPOETRY / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978022800716640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780228007166423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780228007166/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles